result.name: ROOTS

reviews.text:
Very good and nice place! Went there for lunch (only have one hour) and I had plenty of time to enjoy my meal as they are very efficient. The lunch set is quite nice as well as you can have appetizers and / or dessert.
Warmly recommend if you like simple healthy western food.

Great ambiance with great food. Very polite and helpful staff. We went for lunch and unfortunately they were sold out of their chicken dish. Fortunately, every other dish is exquisitely delicious! Definitely worth a visit if you are in the Wan Chai area.

An interesting tour for you to go through the combination of Cantonese and French in every dish. If you are foodie of Cantonese, for sure you will find the shadow of some famous Cantonese dishes and dim sums. Array of favors are mingling with fresh ingredients. All dishes are well made and nicely presented. 
Roots is the name of the restaurant. The chef wants to tell you where the restaurant come from, and tells you its limitless possibilities. Looking forward to their new menu.

Truly great food made with passion and attention to detail. My personal highlight were the chicken sticky rice and lobster risotto. The portions would be great if they were just a bit more substantial. Small cozy environment in the middle of Wan Chai area. Highly recommend.
Unforgettable dining experience. French canto fusion using top quality ingredients. Definitely worth a try. The place is cute too on a quiet street around star street.

result.name: Honbo

reviews.text: One of the best burger places in HK. Juicy patty. Sweet potato fries were nice. A bit on the pricey side.

Honbo is a lesser known local burger joint on Sun Street in Wanchai. Stopped by recently and had good burger for lunch. Opening hours are 12-4pm (lunch) and 5-10pm (dinner) daily. 

Menu is a short list of standard burger types, a few sides and drinks. Burgers are grilled up and served quickly. Seating area is just three side wall tables and one communal style table for 6-8 people. Tables are turned over pretty quickly if you find the place full. 

My recent burger (4 oz.) was pretty good. Beef patty was grilled to medium well but retained good beef flavours. Toppings were fine, bun soft and warm. Sweet potato fries were fried nicely and taste just fine. In short, this was a simple but good burger, just want you want somedays. Will happily return on this basis.

Wow so glad I stumbled across this little haven of delivdeliciousness. Not kidding probably this nicest cheese burger I've EVER HAD. Patty succulent  bun light and fresh sauce finished the job off and the fries were great. Wish this place every success.

Pretty hole in the wall decent burger joint. Serves a tasty burger. 

완전 맛있다!

Probably one of the best hole-in-the-wall burger spots you’d find in Hong Kong. Not hole-in-the-wall prices though. Not insanely expensive but definitely no fast food prices here. Do yourself a favor and get the double, you’re already there.

reviews.text: 這是素食漢堡，蔬菜聞說是即日元朗水耕菜，食落幾新鮮。塊未來肉有一陣陣碳焦香味，而口感的確有食肉嘅感覺。但價錢偏貴，因為正如相片睇，整個漢堡是比較單薄。單以質素來說，值得再次光臨，試試真肉漢堡。
